# CI Workflow Triggers

> **Full docs:** [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) — update that file when changing CI (see [`ci-documentation.mdc`](ci-documentation.mdc)).

## Build & Test — PR (`.github/workflows/build.yml`)

| Job | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Package-lock optional bindings** | **Always runs** — `validate-package-lock-optional-bindings.sh` (no path filter) |
| Detect changes | path filters (`code`, `native`, `typescript`, `helpers`, `examples`, `workflows_*`) |
| Typecheck & lint | **Always runs**; `run-pr-quality.sh` only when `code` or `workflows` — otherwise instant skip |
| Build TypeScript | `build-ts-workspace.sh` + `ci-cache-ts-dist` — when TS/examples paths OR `workflows_ts` |
| Compile native | **Always runs**; compiles debug `.node` only when `native` or `workflows_native` — otherwise instant skip (required-check friendly). Markdown (`**/*.md`) excluded from code filters. |
| Test | **Always runs**; integration tests only when `native`/`typescript`/`helpers`/`examples` — otherwise instant skip |
| Build TypeScript | **Always runs**; builds `dist/` only when TS/examples paths OR `workflows_ts` — otherwise instant skip |

`compile-native` and `build-ts` run **in parallel** after quality passes on GitHub-hosted runners; on **self-hosted** runners `build-ts` waits for `compile-native` because both share one workspace directory. Docs-only and CI skip-gate-only PRs skip compile, TS build, and integration tests while required checks still go green.

Runs on **pull_request → `main`** only. Linux x64 jobs use **`self-hosted`**; macOS/Windows stay on GitHub-hosted runners.

## Build & Test — main (`.github/workflows/build-main.yml`)

Runs on **push → `main`**: **validate-package-lock** → **quality** → reusable release matrix (skip compile on native cache hit) → integration tests.

## Release (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)

Runs on **`release/*` tag push**: **validate-package-lock** → **quality** → reusable build matrix → integration tests → **publish** → **`sync-main-package-lock`** (PR to refresh `package-lock.json` on `main`). See [`scripts/RELEASE.md`](../../scripts/RELEASE.md#package-lockjson-after-release).

Release prep uses `SKIP_LOCK_REFRESH=1` on [`bump-workspace-versions.sh`](../../scripts/ci/bump-workspace-versions.sh); merge the bot **`chore/post-release-package-lock-X.Y.Z`** PR after each tag.

## Reusable workflows & composite actions

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `reusable-build-linux.yml` | Linux release matrix (3 targets) |
| `reusable-build-host.yml` | macOS + Windows release matrix |
| `reusable-test.yml` | Download binding artifact, cache fallback, host Docker tests |
| `actions/ci-build-native-linux` | Cache, compile, verify, upload (Linux) |
| `actions/ci-build-native-host` | Toolchain setup + compile; skip on native cache hit (host OS) |
| `actions/ci-cache-ts-dist` | sdk/signaling `dist/` cache restore/save |
| `actions/ci-run-integration-tests` | coturn sidecar + ci-build test run |
| `actions/native-binding-cache` | Per-target `.node` cache restore/save |

## CI Docker image (`ci` branch)

Rebuild `ghcr.io/.../ci-build:latest` when `docker/ci/Dockerfile` changes — push to **`ci`** branch or **`workflow_dispatch`** on CI Docker image workflow.

## Local validation

```bash
npm run ci:validate:package-lock # stub optional binding lock check
npm run build:native             # host .node for npm test
npm run ci:verify:checks         # PR quality + integration checks (host)
npm run ci:verify:release-ts     # release publish TS path
npm run ci:verify                # alias for ci:verify:checks
npm run ci:verify:linux          # optional: release cross-builds in Docker
```

After changing `docker/ci/Dockerfile`, rebuild (`npm run ci:docker:build`) and push to `ci` branch.
